{"word":"ἱστορέω","slug":"ἱστορέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἱστορέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἵστωρ'><el>ἵστωρ</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to inquire into</i> a thing, <i>to learn by inquiry</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <i>to examine</i>, and in <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> sense, <i>to know</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to inquire of, ask</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be questioned</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li1000'><b>b. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> also <i>to inquire about</i> one, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> dupl. <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to inquire of</i> one <i>about</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to inquire</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to narrate what one has learnt</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}